	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The reasons for it's under use are fairly severe. Nearest bind for most people is three zones away (one of those zones being total KOS), no food, ect. Let's not forget the sheer paranoia surrounding lava some have.<BR>
<BR>
This makes it a simply excellent place for a competent young party to excell.<BR>
<BR>
The only true danger is the fact that imps and elementals tend to wander into the middle of a combat. Since Lavastorm is very rocky, your chances of spotting one of the KOS monsters is small.<BR>
<BR>
Still, for almost unchallanged access to great dungeons (which is what Lavastorm is mostly used for), and completely unchallanged access to low level hunting, Lavastorm can't be beat.<BR>
<BR>
A side note: Lavastorm is also one of the most visually impressive zones I've seen. The lava is simply gunk, but the first view of the zone from the zoning ridge was perfect. Soulsek's Eye is also a must for the budding EverTourist.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
